  <summary date="2018-08-20T18:23:28Z" status="Reported to House without amendment">This bill amends the Federal Deposit Insurance Act, the Bank Holding Company Act of 1956, and the Home Owners' Loan Act to exclude initial client margin funds (i.e., funds lent to a client by a broker to&#160;facilitate a derivatives contract) from leverage-exposure calculations for purposes of determining whether&#160;an insured depository institution, a bank holding company, or a savings and loan holding company&#160;is in compliance&#160;with federal leverage-based capital standards.</summary>
